   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Target Variable: Shares Distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "The target variable `shares` represents how many times an article was shared on social media. Understanding its distribution is critical because:\n",
    "1. It determines if we need transformation (log, sqrt, etc.)\n",
    "2. It helps identify if we have outliers\n",
    "3. It guides our choice of evaluation metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "Key questions:\n",
    "- Is the distribution symmetric or skewed?\n",
    "- What is the typical number of shares?\n",
    "- Are there extreme outliers?"
   ],
   "id": "31676411ff2be019"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-06-20T07:35:33.150791Z",
     "start_time": "2026-06-20T07:35:32.513734Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "# Target variable analysis\n",
    "target = 'shares'\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== Shares Statistics ===\")\n",
    "print(df[target].describe())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSkewness: {df[target].skew():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Kurtosis: {df[target].kurtosis():.2f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create figure with multiple plots\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 1: Histogram (raw values)\n",
    "ax1 = axes[0, 0]\n",
    "ax1.hist(df[target], bins=100, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Distribution of Shares (Raw)')\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel('Number of Shares')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "ax1.axvline(df[target].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {df[target].mean():.0f}')\n",
    "ax1.axvline(df[target].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {df[target].median():.0f}')\n",
    "ax1.legend()\n",
    "ax1.set_xlim(0, df[target].quantile(0.99))  # Zoom to 99th percentile to see distribution better\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 2: Boxplot to show outliers\n",
    "ax2 = axes[0, 1]\n",
    "ax2.boxplot(df[target], vert=True, patch_artist=True)\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Boxplot of Shares')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Number of Shares')\n",
    "ax2.set_xticklabels(['Shares'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 3: Log-transformed histogram\n",
    "ax3 = axes[1, 0]\n",
    "log_shares = np.log1p(df[target])\n",
    "ax3.hist(log_shares, bins=50, color='lightcoral', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax3.set_title('Distribution of Log-Transformed Shares')\n",
    "ax3.set_xlabel('log(1 + Shares)')\n",
    "ax3.set_ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "ax3.axvline(log_shares.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {log_shares.mean():.2f}')\n",
    "ax3.axvline(log_shares.median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {log_shares.median():.2f}')\n",
    "ax3.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 4: QQ plot to check normality\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "ax4 = axes[1, 1]\n",
    "stats.probplot(log_shares, dist=\"norm\", plot=ax4)\n",
    "ax4.set_title('Q-Q Plot of Log-Transformed Shares')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Additional statistics\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== Percentiles ===\")\n",
    "for p in [10, 25, 50, 75, 90, 95, 99]:\n",
    "    print(f\"{p}th percentile: {df[target].quantile(p/100):.0f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nProportion of articles with < 1400 shares: {((df[target] < 1400).sum() / len(df) * 100):.1f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"Proportion of articles with >= 1400 shares: {((df[target] >= 1400).sum() / len(df) * 100):.1f}%\")"
   ],
